cocaine smugglers to turn away from <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> and move more shipments into <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> through ports in the <LOCATION> Netherlands </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. Colombian drug syndicates are believed to supply the vast majority of cocaine distributed in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The Colombian government in August declared war on traffickers. Drug traffickers in turn have waged an almost daily campaign of bombings and killings of officials and journalists in an effort to intimidate the government into ending its crackdown.
