d several truckloads. The guerrillas, who have been fighting the communist government 11 years, say they want to cut off all food and fuel to the capital to force residents to flee. Then, they say they will increase their attacks on the city. When asked where the flour is, merchants at the food markets blow imaginary dust from their fingertips. `` It's gone with the wind'' said one trader.
